description:
&lt;p&gt;This is a unique opportunity to join the Directories and Knowledge Resource Team, based in Norwich, and part of Arden &amp; Gem Commissioning Support Unit (CSU).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Directories and Knowledge Resource Team provide high quality information management services to a range of Clinical Commissioning Groups (CCGs), including a bespoke Knowledge Resource System and several Directories of Services (DoS’), including the 111 DoS.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to recruit a detail focused, customer service skilled and systems minded Directories and Knowledge Resource Administrator into the team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will work with the Directories and Knowledge Resource (DKR) Team in maintaining and developing Knowledge Anglia, the local Directory of Services (DoS), national DoS and related systems;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Act as first point of contact for the department, dealing with routine enquiries in a pleasant and helpful manner, communicating relevant information to stakeholders, referring to others as appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure timely and accurate data entry whilst following maintenance procedures for the service directories (including 111 Dos), Knowledge Anglia and other departmental databases.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Liaise with other staff/organisations to request updates/additions to service directories, content for Knowledge Anglia and other services within the team. Maintain a record of this progress to resolve disputes or queries, referring to the DKR Manager when appropriate.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Edit and maintain clinical information on the Knowledge Anglia website, including converting and maintaining documents in standard site format for addition to the content management system ensuring that all web standards are met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Edit, convert and maintain referral forms on the site required for GP practices, enabling integration with the different clinical systems used and ensuring NPSA and information governance requirements, national standards and accessibility criteria are met.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Editing and updating database records as required, including the identification/location of updated/withdrawn information resources.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide training on the Knowledge Anglia website, the local Directory of Services (DoS), national DoS and related systems, Referral form standards etc. to clients, providers and service users.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Developing and maintaining standard operating procedures for the areas of responsibility, to ensure consistent processes are followed, and to support continuity in the absence of staff.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name - Anna Clark&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title - Directories and Knowledge Resource Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address - anna.clark2@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number - 07884 003435&lt;/p&gt;
